developer_understanding_on_working: The getAlternateStyleSheet method retrieves the alternate style-sheet title for the user agent. It first checks if the title is stored in the hints map using the KEY_ALTERNATE_STYLESHEET key. If it is found, the method returns the title. If not, it falls back to the super class's getAlternateStyleSheet method.
developer_understanding_on_triggering_fr: The triggering frequency of the ALTERNATE_STYLESHEET configuration depends on when the getAlternateStyleSheet method is called in the code. Without further context, it is difficult to determine the exact frequency of triggering.
developer_understanding_on_size_impact: The impact of the ALTERNATE_STYLESHEET configuration option on the system is minimal, as it mainly affects the user agent's display of alternate style-sheets. It does not have a significant impact on the overall system functionality.
